   223→\subsection{Mixed-Precision Allocation Results}
   224→
   225→Table~\ref{tab:mixed_results} reports real perplexity measurements (not estimates) for all configurations. The ILP allocation assigns \texttt{q/k/v\_proj} and \texttt{fc1}/\texttt{fc2} layers to 6-bit (they have the lowest measured sensitivity) while keeping \texttt{out\_proj} and \texttt{lm\_head} at 7-bit.
